fr.apteryx.imageio.dicom
Class DicomReader

Object
  ImageReader
      DicomReader
public class DicomReader
extends ImageReader

The DICOM decoder.

Instances of DicomReader are created using DicomReaderSpi.

Possible inputs are :

  • ImageInputStream
    • for reading either part 10 dicom files, or raw datasets encoded with the little-endian implicit transfer syntax.
  • StorageSCP
    • for reading any dicom object received by the local storage SCP (synchronous listening).
  • ReceivedObject
    • for reading a dicom object received by the local storage SCP (asynchronous listening) or using a Query/Retrieve.

Dicom objects containing no pixel data may be read by calling getDicomMetadata() after setting the input, and without calling image-specific methods like read().

When reading pixel data, the rasters returned by readRaster and the images returned by read contains the pixel values before any grayscale transformed (the "stored values"). DicomMetadata.applyGrayscaleTransformations(BufferedImage, int) may be called afterwards to obtain an image suitable for immediate rendering.

Method Detail

setRawMode

public void setRawMode(boolean b)
If set to true, attribute values of data elements are not interpreted. Values can only be read using DicomMetadata.getAttribute(int) and are always returned as byte[], except for sequences that are returned as a Vector of DataSets, and encapsulated pixel data that are returned as byte[][].

Warning: in raw mode, the whole object is loaded in memory at once, while in normal mode, images are loaded in memory when they are read.

Default is false.
